  "doc_id": "40848",
  "text": "Database searches for BdMoV CRP did not reveal substantial identity with any known protein (Table 1) . When aligned with other benyvirus CRPs, four conserved cysteine residues (aa positions 55, 58, 92 and 94) were identified in their central regions, as described previously ( Supplementary Fig. S2B, CRP) . The CRPs of BdMoV, BNYVV and BSBMV have been shown to function as the weak transgene silencing suppressors in leaf tissue [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ). BdMoV p13 CRP accumulated in the nucleus (data not shown), whereas BNYVV p14 and BSBMV 14-kDa CRPs were distributed in the nucleolus and cytoplasm in which nucleolar localization is not required for its silencing-suppression activity .",
